============================================================

Reviewing the change against each topic:

**Implementation Completeness**: The plan specifies positional check + semantic similarity gate. I implemented both. The one intentional deviation from the plan's proposed code: the plan used exact-match `suppressTexts.has(...)` but I reverted to `startsWith` — which is necessary because multi-line joins (e.g. "PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM Ingredients") derive from the same translation line but aren't ALL_CAPS themselves. Exact match would silently fail to suppress them.

**Code Quality**: The code uses the same patterns as the surrounding file — `rawScored.find((r) => r.text === ...)?.embedding`, optional chaining, inline filter callbacks. Consistent.

**Integration & Refactoring**: The block is a self-contained guard with a clear comment. No adjacent logic needs changing. The rest of the function (threshold computation, dedup, multi-title guard) is untouched as required.

**Codebase Consistency**: `cosineSimilarity` and `rawScored` embeddings were already available at that point in the function. No new imports or utilities added.

The implementation is complete and the tests confirm correctness. No concerns to address.
